snippet.title: Stranger Things 5 | Final Trailer | Netflix
snippet.description:
The wait is almost over. Here is the Final trailer for Stranger Things 5 — the beginning of the end for Hawkins.

This season brings back Millie Bobby Brown, Finn Wolfhard, Noah Schnapp, Sadie Sink, Caleb McLaughlin, Gaten Matarazzo, and David Harbour, alongside Winona Ryder and Maya Hawke.
Expect darker tones, higher stakes, and the most emotional chapter yet.

Stay tuned — the countdown to the Upside Down ends tomorrow.
Subscribe and activate notifications so you don’t miss the premiere of our full cinematic trailer edit.

#StrangerThings5 #Netflix #sadiesink

snippet.title: Return to Silent Hill - Official Trailer (2026) Hannah Emily Anderson, Jeremy Irvine, Robert Strange
snippet.description:
Watch the Official Trailer for Return to Silent Hill, an upcoming action horror film distributed by Konami and Cineverse. Witness the thriller that's inspired by the iconic video game franchise with Return to Silent Hill, in theaters on January 23, 2026.

When a mysterious letter calls him back to Silent Hill searching for his lost love, James finds a once-recognizable town and encounters figures both familiar and new and begins to question his own sanity.

Return to Silent Hill stars Hannah Emily Anderson, Jeremy Irvine, Robert Strange, Evie Templeton, Pearse Egan, Eve Macklin, Emily Carding, and more. The film is directed by Christophe Gans and written by Christophe Gans, Hiroyuki Owaku, and William Josef Schneider. 

Return to Silent Hill is in theaters on January 23, 2026.

The Stranger Things Season 5 Trailer delivers the most intense look yet at the final chapter of Netflix’s global phenomenon. Stranger Things is an American science fiction horror drama television series created by the Duffer Brothers for Netflix. Produced by Monkey Massacre Productions and 21 Laps Entertainment, the first season was released on Netflix on July 15, 2016. The second and third season followed in October 2017 and July 2019 respectively, and the fourth season aired in two parts in May and July 2022. In February 2022, Stranger Things was renewed for a fifth and final season.
Set in the 1980s, the series centers around the residents of the fictional small town of Hawkins, Indiana, as they are plagued by a hostile alternate dimension known as the Upside Down, after a nearby human experimentation facility opens a gateway between it and the normal world. The ensemble cast includes Winona Ryder, David Harbour, Finn Wolfhard, Millie Bobby Brown, Gaten Matarazzo, Caleb McLaughlin, Natalia Dyer, Charlie Heaton, Cara Buono, Matthew Modine, Noah Schnapp, Sadie Sink, Joe Keery, Dacre Montgomery, Sean Astin, Paul Reiser, Maya Hawke, Priah Ferguson and Brett Gelman. Stranger Things trailer concept, Stranger Things Season 5, Stranger Things Season 5 trailer,  The Duffer Brothers developed Stranger Things as a mix of investigative drama and supernatural elements portrayed with horror and childlike sensibilities, while infusing references to the pop culture of the 1980s. Several thematic and directorial elements were inspired by the works of Steven Spielberg, John Carpenter, David Lynch, Stephen King, Wes Craven and H. P. Lovecraft. They also took inspiration from experiments conducted during the Cold War and conspiracy theories involving secret government programs.
One of Netflix's flagship series, Stranger Things has attracted record viewership on the streaming platform. Stranger Things Season 5 teaser trailer.It has been critically acclaimed for its characterization, atmosphere, acting, soundtrack, directing, writing, and homages to 1980s films. It has received numerous nominations and awards. An animated spin-off series, developed by Eric Robles and produced by Flying Bark Productions, is in development.

snippet.description:
#themandalorian #leakedtrailer #starwarscelebration  

Watch the 'FAN (CONCEPT) Trailer Concept' For Star Wars The Mandalorian And Grogu (2026)  (More Info About This Video Down Below!)

▶️ Watch More Concept Trailers:

SOLO 2: A Star Wars Story Trailer - https://youtu.be/vCmBvA1j68I 👈

AHSOKA Season 2 Trailer -  https://youtu.be/jQ289yp9c6o 👈

Crimson Dawn : A Star Wars Story Trailer -  https://youtu.be/GtKwWMqrjV8 👈

"The Mandalorian & Grogu (2026)" marks the Mandalorian saga’s thrilling return to the big screen under the visionary direction of Jon Favreau, with a screenplay co-written by Favreau and Dave Filoni. This highly anticipated film transports fan-favorite duo Din Djarin and Grogu from their Disney+ appearances into a cinematic scale adventure. Pedro Pascal reprises his role as the stoic Din Djarin, while Grogu continues to captivate audiences through a blend of animatronics, puppetry, and advanced visual effects.

Joining Pascal and Grogu is an esteemed ensemble cast: Sigourney Weaver stars as a commanding New Republic colonel named Ward, who oversees critical missions following the fall of the Empire. Jeremy Allen White voices the now-grown Rotta the Hutt—once Jabba’s son—taking him in a new, muscular gladiator direction. Jonny Coyne returns as the imposing Imperial warlord leading remnants of the Empire, while characters like Garazeb “Zeb” Orrelios and members of the Anzellan species make appearances, deepening the narrative continuity with the Disney+ series.

Scheduled for release on May 22, 2026, "The Mandalorian & Grogu" serves as the first theatrical installment in the Star Wars franchise since The Rise of Skywalker (2019). Although a trailer has not yet been released to the public, exclusive footage debuted at D23 2024 and Star Wars Celebration 2025, offering glimpses of Grogu training, AT-ATs in snowy terrain, and exciting action sequences. Directed and produced by Favreau, with Kathleen Kennedy and Dave Filoni also at the helm, the film promises to deliver a standalone cinematic experience that both longtime fans and newcomers can enjoy.

snippet.title: Simply Red - Holding Back The Years (Live from Santiago)
snippet.description:
Simply Red - Holding Back The Years (Live from Santiago)

Simply Red are thrilled to announce 'Recollections', their brand-new album celebrating 40 incredible years! Featuring 40 newly recorded versions of their most loved songs, the album will be available digitally, on 4LP vinyl, as a 3CD set, and as a 2LP highlights edition, out November 21. Pre-order it here: https://SimplyRed.lnk.to/RecollectionsYT

Tickets for the Simply Red 40th Anniversary Tour are available now! Get yours at https://www.simplyred.com

Subscribe to Simply Red - https://www.youtube.com/@simplyred/featured?sub_confirmation=1

Follow Simply Red:
https://www.facebook.com/simplyred/
https://twitter.com/SimplyRedHQ
https://instagram.com/simplyredofficial
https://www.tiktok.com/@simplyredofficial
https://www.threads.net/@simplyredofficial

Simply Red have over a billion hits on YouTube, have sold over 60 million albums worldwide, 5 going to number one in the UK. Their 1991 classic Stars was the best-selling album for two years running in Britain and Europe. They have had two US Billboard chart toppers with classic singles Holding Back The Years and If You Don’t Know Me By Now. Every Simply Red studio album has been a UK top ten (with previous release Big Love reaching number 4 in 2015). Hucknall has been the songwriter and bandleader since the beginning in 1985.

Lyrics
Holding back the years
Thinking of the fear I've had so long
When somebody hears
Listen to the fear that's gone
Strangled by the wishes of pater
Hoping for the arms of mater
Get to me the sooner or later

I'll keep holding on
I'll keep holding on

Holding back the years
Chance for me to escape from all I've known
Holding back the tears
Cause nothing here has grown
I've wasted all my tears
Wasted all those years
And nothing had the chance to be good
Nothing ever could yeah, oh

I'll keep holding on
I'll keep holding on
I'll keep holding on
I'll keep holding on
So tight

I've wasted all my tears
Wasted all of those years
And nothing had the chance to be good
Cause nothing ever could, oh, yeah
Oh...

I'll keep holding on
I'll keep holding on
I'll keep holding on
I'll keep holding on
Holding, holding, holding

That's all I have today
It's all I have to say

#SimplyRed #Recollections #HoldingBackTheYears

“We Are The World” was originally released on March 7, 1985. The song was produced by Quincy Jones and written by Michael Jackson and Lionel Richie. It was recorded in Los Angeles, CA, with Stevie Wonder, Paul Simon, Kenny Rogers, Tina Turner, Billy Joel, Diana Ross, Dionne, Warwick, Bruce Springsteen, Bob Dylan, Ray Charles, Bette Midler, Smokey Robinson, and more.

A remastered and Spatial Audio version of “We Are The World” was released on Friday, November 21, 2025 to commemorate 40 years of “We Are The World.”

snippet.title: intro - Peso Pluma & Tito Double P (Video Oficial)
snippet.description:
Doble P Records©

• ESCUCHA / LISTEN:
https://www.doublepmusic.com/intr

•LETRA
Voy por la noche arriba en el porsche
Recorriendo todos los pinches puteros
Aveces de dolce
Y las que me conocen
Dos tragos de whisky me dicen te quiero

Ya son las doce cerramos con broche
Traigo unas ganas y aquí voy pal cielo
Que el billete se note y un polvo sin corte
La piki le jala y le mama el refuego

Y ando bien lokote
fajada la corta
Bañadas las cachas
Brillan los diamantones se ven rosas

Vieran que bonito el chirris y la mota
Salí malandro de lejos
ahuevo yo sé que se nota

Me pongo travieso
Se encima la zorra
Súbete mami verás que se siente bien dura la cosa

Otra noche que
Nos pasamos de copas
Le pego unos baises
Me pide le pase el humito en la boca

Pasaron dos noches quiero que rebote
Unos besotes donde más yo quiero
Otro pal rebote ya pasan las 12
Un wiskacho pa bajarme ese polvo bueno

No te me aloques pégate unos toques
Ya prendí el gallón de ese pinche veneno
Si soy bien coqueto pero a ti te quiero
Vámonos juntitos de nuevo pal cielo

ando bien lokote
fajada la corta
Bañadas las cachas
Brillan los diamantones se ven rosas

Vieran que bonito el chirris y la mota
Salí malandro de lejos
ahuevo yo sé que se nota

Me pongo travieso
Sexy mamasota
Y Súbete mami verás que se siente muy dura la cosa

Otra noche que
la pasamos de poca
me pegué unos baisones
Y me pide que le pase el humo en la boca
